Cape Town Popular singer and actor Dumi Masilela has been killed during a hijacking in Tembisa, Ekurhuleni.Dumi Masilela played the role of Sifiso Ngema on the popular e.tv soapie.He took to acting after he was involved in a car accident that saw him quitting his professional soccer career.Minister of Arts and Culture Nathi Mthethwa has expressed his condolences on Twitter. &#8220;It is with absolute shock and dismay that we received the news of Rhythm City star Dumi Masilela&#8217;s sudden and tragic passing,&#8221; said Arts and Culture Minister Nathi Mthethwa.His assailants drove away in his car.